docs.abstract: Several banking trade groups have sued the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau, claiming it has exceeded its authority with anti-discrimination enforcement.
docs.snippet: Several banking trade groups have sued the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau, claiming it has exceeded its authority with anti-discrimination enforcement.
docs.lead_paragraph: Since George Floyd’s murder by the police in 2020 refocused public attention on racism in the United States, regulators — including those appointed by President Biden to oversee financial institutions — have vowed to prioritize the task of rooting out discrimination. But banks are now accusing one of them of going too far.

headline.main: Banks Accuse Consumer Regulator of Abuse of Power
headline.print_headline: Banks Accuse Consumer Agency of Abusing Power

docs.abstract: While compellingly readable, Peniel E. Joseph’s “The Third Reconstruction” overstates the impact of the recent reckoning over racial justice.
docs.snippet: While compellingly readable, Peniel E. Joseph’s “The Third Reconstruction” overstates the impact of the recent reckoning over racial justice.
docs.lead_paragraph: If racial progress in America tends to arrive in waves, much of it has come in the form of two crashing breakers: the First Reconstruction, which ended slavery after the Civil War, and the Second, which ended Jim Crow segregation a century later. The historian Peniel E. Joseph believes we have just witnessed a third such moment, bracketed by Barack Obama’s election in 2008 and the wake of George Floyd’s murder in 2020.

headline.main: A Premature Victory Lap for Black Lives Matter

keywords.value: The Third Reconstruction: America's Struggle for Racial Justice in the Twenty-First Century (Book)

docs.abstract: Thomas Lane pleaded guilty in May to a charge of second-degree manslaughter. He is already serving a federal sentence for violating Mr. Floyd’s civil rights.

docs.lead_paragraph: A former Minneapolis police officer, Thomas Lane, was sentenced to three years in prison on Wednesday for his role in the killing of George Floyd in 2020.

headline.main: Former Minneapolis Officer Sentenced to Three Years in George Floyd Case
headline.print_headline: Ex-Officer in Minneapolis Gets 3 Years in Floyd Case
